By BO Editorial CollectiveBlack Opinion turns 1 years old today. With that, we continue to implore Black people to think for themselves. Thus we are running a writing competition under the following details: Who is the enemy of black liberation in South Africa?1. Jacob Zuma? 2. The Guptas? 3. White monopoly capital/those who stole land of blacks?In 300 to 1000 words justify your answer.All submissions will be published in Black Opinion without being edited.The deadline is Wednesday, April 12, 2017. The winning contribution stands to be awarded R1000 cash. Winning contribution will be selected by the Black Opinion Editorial Collective.Send responses to: editor@blackopinion.co.za